.TH nfsportmon 8
.SH NAME
\*Lnfsportmon\*L - Turns the port monitor on or off
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\*L/usr/sbin/nfsportmon \*Voption\*O
.SH FLAGS
.VL 4m
.LI "\*Lon\*O"
Turns on the port monitor.
.LI "\*Loff\*O"
Turns off the port monitor.
.LE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "nfsportmon command"
.iX "port monitor" "turning on the"
.iX "port monitor" "turning off the"
The \*Lnfsportmon\*O
command turns the port monitor on or off at the kernel level.
By default,
the port monitor is turned off.
.PP
When the port monitor is on,
NFS server port checking is activated.
This checking increases system security by
ensuring that file access requests were
generated by the client kernel rather than by
a forged application program, for example.
.PP
Only the superuser or root can run \*Lnfsportmon\*O.
